.TH "vmw_bo_dirty_scan_mkwrite" 9 "vmw_bo_dirty_scan_mkwrite" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_bo_dirty_scan_mkwrite \- Reset the mkwrite dirty-tracking method
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vmw_bo_dirty_scan_mkwrite
.BI "(struct vmw_buffer_object *vbo "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vbo" 12
The buffer object to scan
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write-protect pages written to so that consecutive write accesses will
trigger a call to mkwrite.

This function may change the dirty-tracking method.
